first time at preschool my year old son will be starting preschool august th he seems very excited and keeps telling us he wants to go to school i just don't think he realizes that me and daddy won't be staying with him what are some ways to prepare him for that first day and help him not to cry tell him you will not be staying with him show him a clock and tell him as well as show him when you will drop him off and when he will come home the first day or so he may cry it is always boys that cry in my years of kindergarten i have never had a girl cry yet read some books about going to school the berenstain bears have one there is also ms bindergarten gets ready for kindergarten talk about the things he will do there paint play dough the block center etc he is going to learn songs fingerplays and go on the jungle gym don't let him see you cry hold back the tears until you get outside and stay parked until your eyes are clear the main thing is to let him know you will be there every single day and he will have so much fun and he will i just hope he has an absolutely wonderful teacher good luck Kindergarten Avenue Q Kodocha Jon Secada Shaggy dog story Recess (TV series) About a Boy Scenes from a Memory The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Social rule Cliff Richard Pok__mon Live! The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame's 500 Songs that Shaped Rock and Roll The Amber Spyglass Miss Saigon Episodes of Lost (Season 1) The Adventures of Pete & Pete The Contender (television series) Pitaten The Ashlee Simpson Show Bart chalkboard gags Murdock-Portal Elementary School Berenstain Bears Kender Piccolo Junior Saga The Emancipation of Mimi One Tree Hill (TV series) Education in Taiwan The Shining (film) Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Milton H. Erickson AFI 100 Years series She Loves You The Notorious B.I.G. Education in the United States Independent Schools Association of the Southwest The Freewheelin' Bob Dylan The Beatles discography The Catcher in the Rye Friends I Don't 